      "bodyText": "LIVE ON SOLANA — THE FIRST TRUSTLESS SIGNING NETWORK →\nWhat is Ika\nAgents\nUse Cases\nCompare\nDocs\nStart Building\nNOW LIVE ON SOLANA\nEvery chain is yours.\n\nIka gives your code native signing power across chains.\n\nMove policy on one side, Bitcoin, Ethereum, Solana, and more on the other. Under a second. No bridge custody. No exposed master key. Just signatures that settle where the capital already lives.\n\nStart Building →\nRead the Docs\nLATENCY\n< 1s\nSECURITY\n0 keys held\nREACH\nAny chain\nPROGRAMMABLE SIGNING CORE\nMove policy → native execution\n\nOne control plane routes real signatures into the chain where capital already sits.\n\nPROGRAMMABLE POLICIES\nTRUSTLESS SIGNATURES\nSIGNING ROUTE\nSolana → Bitcoin\n\nDirected execution rails instead of bridge hops, with native settlement at the edge.\n\nEXECUTION STATE\nSub-second quorum\n\nHundreds of nodes coordinate one approval surface while the key stays split the whole time.\n\n10,000×\nFaster than any MPC network\n< 1s\nTime to sign, any chain\n100+\nNodes. Zero hold your key.\n\nARCHITECTURE\n\nThe key never becomes a liability.\n\nIka uses 2PC-MPC so signing is computed jointly without reconstructing the private key in one place. That matters because most systems fail at the control point. They may decentralize governance language, but key control still collapses back to a small group of signers. Ika changes the control model itself.\n\n01 — SPEED\nWhile they\nwait, you ship.\n\nLegacy MPC: 30 seconds. Ika: under one. That's not an improvement. That's a differen"
